The various meanings for answer choices could include: A) marks made by pressing or stamping something into a surface. B) imitating a person or animal for entertainment. C) the number of times an ad is viewed by an audience. D) a memory  or strong effect on someone's mind.

text_answer.content: I suggest adjusting the content of the passage to Luna falling asleep very late, but not staying up all night, as this sets a wrong tone of acceptance for students at this age regarding incomplete schoolwork! Additionally, the word, "light," is too easy for the multiple meanings word. I suggest "drift(ed)" from paragraph 4. Answer choice options could include: A) a change in course for a boat or airplane due to winds. B) the general meaning of someone's remarks or argument. C) a huge mass of snow or leaves piled up when blown by wind. D) carried slowly by air current or wind

text_answer.content: I think the message of students "sneaking" into the science lab, and being in the school halls "well after the final bell," sends the wrong message. Additionally, the tone bordered on disrespect toward authority (the principal), instead of promoting collaboration with an authority figure, as well. These parts of the story could be reworked a bit and the story would still have value, but it isn't wise to advocate breaking school rules to students to prove a point (no matter how "valuable"). This passage could also be accessible for 5th graders.
